**About Us**

Nitro Crushing is a leading provider of mobile crushing, screening, and
conveying solutions across Queensland. Since 2007, we\'ve built a strong
reputation for delivering high-quality, efficient, and reliable services
to the mining, quarrying, and civil construction industries. With a
modern fleet of well-maintained machinery and a team of experienced
professionals, we are committed to safety, performance, and innovation
in every project we undertake.

**About the Role**

We are currently seeking an experienced **Quarry Supervisor** to join
our team. This is an excellent opportunity for a Cairns, Mackay or
Brisbane based resident to step into a leadership role and drive
productivity in a fast-paced, safety-focused environment.

This position is offered on a FIFO or DIDO basis.

As a **Quarry Supervisor**, you will be responsible for overseeing
day-to-day quarry operations, ensuring production targets are met,
maintaining equipment reliability, and leading a team to uphold the
highest safety and operational standards.

**Key Responsibilities:**

-   Supervise and coordinate mobile crushing operations, ensuring
    efficiency and compliance with safety standards.

-   Operate and oversee mobile crushing equipment, including jaw and
    cone crushers, screens, and conveyors.

-   Lead, train, and mentor a team of maintainer/operators, fostering a
    strong safety and performance culture.

-   Conduct routine inspections, identify operational issues, and assist
    with maintenance tasks such as screen changes, wear part
    replacements, and roller/skirting adjustments.

-   Ensure a clean, level, and well-maintained work area, including
    proper material blending and effective benching.

-   Communicate effectively with site management and stakeholders to
    optimise operations.

**What We're Looking For:**

Previous experience in a **supervisory role** within mobile crushing,
quarrying, or mining operations.\
Strong knowledge of **mobile crushing equipment** operation and
maintenance.\
A current open **Australian driver's license** (mandatory).\
Nationally accredited **tickets for wheel loader and/or excavator
operation**.\
Strong leadership skills with the ability to motivate and develop team
members.\
A proactive approach to **safety, compliance, and operational
excellence**.\
Physical fitness and the ability to perform manual labour when required.

This role offers a fantastic opportunity to join a well-established
company that values its people and prioritises safety and efficiency.

